1. Software version: ruby 1.8.7 (2011-12-28 patchlevel 357)
                     gem version 1.3.5
                     mysql version 5.1.41

2. Import gems: 'cradle.gems' is a gems list file exported by RVM(Ruby Version Manager).
                use command: $ rvm gemset import cradle.gems

                When importing cradle.gems, it will must appear some errors on 'fiveruns-memcache-client' and 'starling-starling'.
                use command: $ sudo install fiveruns-memcache-client starling-starling --source http://gems.github.com

              * In windows, there is no RVM which can be used. We have to import all gems manually.

3. Import database: Create two database named 'cradle_jp' and 'cradle_cn' in msyql.
                    In '<cradle directory>/db', there are two files 'cor-jp-20110531.sql' and 'cor-cn-20110531.sql'.
                    Import into the corresponding database.
                    Database configuration is 'database.yml' in '<cradle directory>/config'.

4. Start server: use commands: $ starling -d -p 22122 -P tmp/pids/starling.pid -L log/starling.log -q tmp/
                               $ script/server

5. Use firefox to browse 'http://localhost:3000'.

